reviews.review_text:
Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1994-10-19 Nice sound, thanks.

2 cents: I remember this show. Stella Blue with Jer going off at the end transcending with the boys sounding like an electronic orchestra reaching deep into the depths and rising into pure white blue stellar light then bringing it down with that cool hawaiian?  sound Jer started doing in the late nineties which turns into one of the most perfect lead-ins into> Sugar Mags that builds into a rocking crescendo spiraling like an out of control skeletal carousel (ladies and gentlemen, all aboard!) whirling into space just before the break before the SSDD ending...

Ah, the memories. Not an incredible show in whole, but a very good one with the SB>SM being spectacular.
jerry so far I just had to write Jerry was hot! singing Bertha
